One persisted `Settings` value as the single source of truth, wrapped in one observable store — but consumers subscribe to **slices**, not the whole blob. So the part that registers the hotkey reacts only to hotkey changes, the overlay reacts only to shortcut changes, and the AI subsystem reacts only to model changes. None of them know about each other.

